nts1.n: A Month of Sundays w/ Bill Spencer - Dutch Rap Special
nts1.d:
Bill Spencer shares weekend recordings from his living room studio in Detroit, Michigan, from where he brings a range of soulful jazz rock, and ambient sounds, spanning to electronica and psychedelic dub.
From the host: "Dutch soundcloud rap from 2017-2022"

A little bit sweet, a little bit sad, a little bit silly - Lupini keeps it (mainly) horizontal with a mix of dubwise sounds, psychedelic rock, synth-pop and new wave.
From the host: "happy solstice! in the longest night, lupini keeps it horizontal and in the winter interior with a selection of some of her most-played releases of 2025"

nts1.n: AD 93 w/ enya and Daniel S. Evans
nts1.d:
Two hours of leftfield dance and beyond every month from AD 93 boss Tasker and guests.
Old 88 Transition shows available on the archive.

nts1.n: DEATH IS NOT THE END - Christmas in Heaven: Seasonal Gospel & Blues
nts1.d:
Death Is Not The End digs up the oldest of the old, serving up your gospel, blues and folk with a crackle. Hear the dust.
From the host: "2hrs of festive gospel and blues records from the 1920s through to the early 1970s"

Kyle Parker of the Los Angeles-based ambient project Infinite Body shares an hour of serene & melancholic piano, including a piece from his new album. Scattered throughout are existential spoken word interludes sampled out of context from across the internet.

Batukizer DJs will take you on deep dives exploring  some of the many legacies and depths of Brazilian dance floor music. Tune in for musical journeys inspired by nature, spirituality, art, history and regional culture, delivered with passion by the Brazilian/Danish vinyl fanatics based in Copenhagen and sometimes Brazil.
System Olympia joins us for an hour a month.

nts1.d: Cosmo Vitelli & DJ Sundae head up the monthly hour-long slot for No Weapon Is Absolute, direct from Paris…

In Iceland, Thomas Stankiewicz contemplates the constant flux of the elements. A composer & musician in his own right, he selectively weaves in between soundtracks, classical music, and evocative ambient sounds, symphonically unveiling untold stories from past and future…
@tommmasi

nts2.d: The true progenitors of the darkest art: heavy metal. Birthed in the industrial fug of 1960s Birmingham, Black Sabbath set themselves apart from other rock bands of the era, espousing occult themes in their lyrics, and playing their guitars at a menacing downtune.
All flavours of acoustic & historical nuggets from Andras - Melbourne production wiz, composer & sleuth of musical ephemera…
This edition of Rio Doce focuses on songs from independence in Africa and the anti racist movement in Brazil from the last 60 years.

nts2.n: DOING TIME - Bhangra Special w/ Munir & Fuji’s Bazaar (R)
nts2.d: Veteran NTS host Hampus brings you Doing Time: a genre-agnostic monthly trip through quality records from around the world’s past and present, featuring regular appearances from musical friends and family.
Eazy-breezy dancefloor eclecticism from the DC wonder duo…

Two hours of classics and lesser known gems from a towering figure in electronic music. 
Selected by Unified Goods, celebrating the launch of AFX50 - 40 handpicked Aphex Twin Objects to mark Richard James’ 50th Birthday. https://unifiedgoods.com/
Música sentimental for all the sad girls and sad boys.

subtle.d:
Hailing from Mumbai, now living in London, Chaitu is energised by the UK sound and scene.

With a love of all things weird, weighty and groovy; his mixes and productions bridge electro, techno, breaks, UKG and Jungle, with sprinklings of everything in between.

Chaitu champions provocative beats that break down the barriers of style, genre and expectation, all while keeping you moving.

Saraphim (aka RNS & RDubz) are two Essex based Producer/DJ’s currently focused on Dubstep & the 140 spectrum, mixing ethnical and grime influences into their music. You can expect anything from deep and melodic meditative vibes to high energy driven music.
London based DJ who enjoys exploring the darker, bassier corners of Jungle, Breaks, Techno and Drum & Bass, especially when it is laced with a bit of acid.

Wheel2Wheel is a Manchester based event which primarily focuses on the underground sectors to genres such as UK Garage, House, Tech House, Electro, Minimal and Breakbeat. Co-Founder Freddie SJ hosts the first hour of the show, sharing his favourites as well as recent digs across the genres, and then invites fellow friends, artists and nights from the scene to present hour-long guest mixes which aims to shine a light on their sound and who they are!


With hours of Discogs screen-time under his belt and a passion for 90's & early 00's releases, expect to hear a variety of different tunes from Labels you may have never heard of and Countries you might not expect!


Give us a follow on Instagram to hear about our upcoming events and all other things music related! @wheel2wheel.mcr

subtle.n: The Ice Box Sessions with Frigid

subtle.d: Japanese DJ from Tokyo, currently living in London.  Based on UK club music, but straddles other genres such as dancehall, reggaeton, gqom and amapiano.

Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".

Kishan is a DJ and Producer currently based in London. Actively involved in the music scene already, he produces and mixes a wide range of genres including UK Garage, Drum & Bass, House, Disco and Afrobeat.

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy
